'''Mageina Tovah''' (born July 26, 1979) is an [[United States|American]] actress. She is best known for her roles as Glynis Figliola in the [[television series]] ''[[Joan of Arcadia]]'' (2003–2005) and as Ursula Ditkovich in [[Spider-Man in film#Sam Raimi films|Sam Raimi's ''Spider-Man'' trilogy]].
==Early life== Tovah was born '''Mageina Tovah Begtrup''' in [[Honolulu, Hawaii]], where her father was a [[US Army]] psychiatrist in the Green Berets, and her mother was an Army physical therapist. Her family later settled for a time in [[Clarksville, Tennessee]], before moving to [[Nashville, Tennessee|Nashville]]. Mageina attended [[Martin Luther King Magnet at Pearl High School|Martin Luther King Junior Magnet High School]] in Nashville. She skipped a year of high school, taking both her Junior year of honors English and her Senior year of AP English at the same time. She graduated from high school at the age of 16. For college, Mageina started at [[The California Institute of the Arts]], and graduated magna cum laude from [[University of Southern California|USC]] in three and a half years. She later moved to [[New York City]] and [[Los Angeles, California|Los Angeles]]. She is [[Jewish]].<ref>https://www.juf.org/celebrities/celebrity.aspx?id=24624</ref><ref>https://twitter.com/mageina/status/518159500432658433</ref><ref>http://www.listal.com/mageina-tovah</ref>
==Career== Tovah had a recurring role on ''Joan of Arcadia'' (2003–2005). Her television work also includes guest roles on a number of TV shows. These include ''[[Buffy the Vampire Slayer]]'', ''[[NYPD Blue]]'', ''[[Six Feet Under (TV series)|Six Feet Under]]'', ''[[The Shield]]'', ''[[Cold Case]]'', [[“Shameless,”]]''[[Crossing Jordan]]'', ''[[American Horror Story]]'', ''[[Private Practice (TV series)|Private Practice]]'', and ''[[The Magicians (U.S. TV series)|The Magicians]]''. Tovah's [[feature film]] work includes roles in ''[[The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie]]'', ''Dark Heart'', ''[[Failure to Launch]]'', ''[[Bickford Shmeckler's Cool Ideas]]'', and a recurring role as Ursula Ditkovich in the films ''[[Spider-Man 2]]'' and ''[[Spider-Man 3]]''.
Tovah also made an appearance in the [[Jonas Åkerlund]]-directed [[music video]] for [[Christina Aguilera]]'s hit song "[[Beautiful (Christina Aguilera song)|Beautiful]]".
